      "blocks": {
        "rich_text_HzbnnX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>10 Facts about Lab Grown Diamonds</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_KpTLT7": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_PbLPK6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Lately, some of the biggest celebrities have been spotted wearing <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/lab-grown-diamond\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown Diamond\">Lab Grown Diamond</a> Jewelry, both in magazines and on red carpets. From Zendaya’s sparkling Lab Grown Diamond Necklace at the Oscars to Emma Watson’s sustainable jewelry at film premieres, A-listers are proving that luxury need not come at the cost of the environment. The shift from Natural Diamonds to Lab Grown Diamonds is clear. If celebrities who set fashion trends are choosing Lab Grown Diamonds, it is because these diamonds have the same sparkle.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_RdjgXi": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Are Lab Grown Diamonds?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Are Lab Grown Diamonds?</h2><p>Lab Grown Diamonds are created using advanced technology in labs, mimicking the same environment in which natural diamonds are formed. They are disrupting the diamond industry. They are created using either of two methods: High Pressure High Temperature (HPHT) or Chemical Vapor Deposition (CVD). In both methods, the process starts with a diamond 'seed', which then crystallizes into a rough diamond.</p>",
            "custom_id": "intro"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kcQDJb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1. Lab Grown Diamonds: As Real As Mined Diamonds",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>1. Lab Grown Diamonds: As Real As Mined Diamonds</h2>",
            "custom_id": "real"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_XcF4rg": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/1_259e3461-1e83-446c-a7b3-014fe7084fa3.jpg",
            "text": "<p>First things first, let’s answer the most common question: are lab grown diamonds real? Physically, chemically, and optically, a lab grown diamond is the same as a naturally mined diamond. A Lab Grown Diamond is as true as a Mined Diamond. They are made in only a few weeks, unlike natural diamonds, which take billions of years to form. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_riTqXr": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The shine is the same as natural diamonds, and they also rank the same on the Mohs Scale of hardness, proving that they are real diamonds. Without specialized equipment, even gemologists cannot tell them apart.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_KpYECE": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "2. Certified and Graded Just Like Natural Diamonds",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>2. Certified and Graded Just Like Natural Diamonds</h2>",
            "custom_id": "certified"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_kAzJKr": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Certificate_08b7c047-ef5d-4e20-a834-3f312b71856e.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Since Lab Grown Diamonds are 100% Real Diamonds, they are also certified just like Natural Diamonds. Two of the most popular certifying institutions are the International Gemological Institute (IGI) and Solitaire Gemological Laboratories (SGL). While buying diamond jewelry, it is important to get certified pieces as these certifications help you verify the details provided by the seller. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_hpdbUP": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Lab Grown Diamond certificates indicate the cut (shape), color, clarity, and most importantly, the carat (weight of the diamond). To understand more about these certifications, we have created guides for you to know all about <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/blogs/stories/how-to-read-your-igi-certificate\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"IGI Certificate\">IGI</a> and <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/blogs/stories/sgl-certification-and-how-to-read-it\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"SGL Certificate\">SGL</a> certifications. At Lucira, all diamond jewelry is IGI and SGL certified.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mVzMCt": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "3. Same physical and chemical properties as Mined Diamonds",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>3. Same physical and chemical properties as Mined Diamonds</h2>",
            "custom_id": "properties"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_87xYCm": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/LGD_vs_MD.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Lab Grown Diamonds share the same physical and chemical properties as Mined Diamonds. <br/>Only specialized equipment can distinguish a Lab Grown Diamond from a Mined Diamond, as they shine the same and have the same qualities. The carbon structure is identical, with the same hardness. The only difference between Lab Grown and Mined Diamonds is their origin.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_q4VxH8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "4. More Customization Options",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>4. More Customization Options</h2>",
            "custom_id": "custom"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_frRnYM": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Customisation.jpg",
            "text": "<p>If you are facing a dilemma of Natural vs Lab Diamond and you want to see what differs Lab Grown Diamonds design-wise from Natural Diamonds, then you are at the right place.  Recent trends are showcasing what Lab Grown Diamonds have to offer, apart from already being more affordable. Lab Grown Diamonds allow you to create a diamond exactly the way you want it, the shape, the size, the color, and even matching multi-stone jewelry sets. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AET4jC": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>For instance, if you want a set of diamond <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/all-earrings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Earrings\">earrings</a> with a matching <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/pendant-necklaces\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Pendant Necklace\">pendant necklace</a>, it is nearly impossible to find identical Natural Diamonds, but easy for Lab Grown Diamond jewelers to craft exactly what you want.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_tgEhQ9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "5. Bigger Diamonds At A Lesser Budget",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>5. Bigger Diamonds At A Lesser Budget</h2><p>Buying Lab Grown Diamond jewelry is a smart move because you always get bigger diamonds at a lower budget. Lab Grown Diamonds are created in labs, eliminating mining costs and reducing labor costs. The efficiency of producing these diamonds makes them cost 60–85% less than naturally mined diamonds.</p>",
            "custom_id": "budget"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_TVTKrb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "6. Sustainably Created",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>6. Sustainably Created</h2>",
            "custom_id": "sustainable"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_wfH3b6": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Sustainability_56cb7b2e-f509-4a5b-a0e6-e67d1c467391.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Lab Grown Diamonds have become a popular choice over the last few decades because they are the perfect alternative to Naturally Mined Diamonds with equal beauty, while being more sustainable. Mining natural diamonds leads to soil erosion, habitat loss, and other environmental damage. Lab Grown Diamonds create a much smaller carbon footprint.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_UVFHMJ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "7. More Ethical",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>7. More Ethical</h2>",
            "custom_id": "ethical"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_dTiiBx": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/7_79b9cb2b-2f81-4375-a8cf-96141736d946.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Naturally Mined Diamonds are often called blood diamonds. This is because in some cases, diamonds are mined in war zones to fund conflicts, encouraging violence. Beyond that, mining deteriorates the health of mineworkers. Lab Grown Diamonds are created ethically, with brands increasingly introducing measures to become more environmentally sustainable.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_7HbeXL": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "8. Lesser Flaws! ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>8. Lesser Flaws! </h2><p>Lab grown diamonds are created in a more controlled environment, causing lesser inclusions and flaws. With more clarity, they provide a better quality, looking flawless. </p>",
            "custom_id": "flaws"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kUpAyY": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "9. They Are The Future Of Diamonds",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>9. They Are The Future Of Diamonds</h2>",
            "custom_id": "future"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_c9wyjT": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Future_of_LGD.jpg",
            "text": "<p>The growing demand and acceptance of Lab Grown Diamonds by consumers shows that the future of the jewelry industry will be dominated by them for their sustainability and cost benefits, while being equally stunning as naturally Mined Diamonds.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_hjh3M4": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "10. Smarter Value Over Resale ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>10. Smarter Value Over Resale </h2><p>While the resale value of diamonds is generally low, whether Natural or Lab Grown, Lab Grown Diamonds offer smarter upfront value by letting you buy more at a fraction of the cost.</p>",
            "custom_id": "value"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_QkQ9Md": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Lab Grown Diamonds truly offer everything affordability, beauty, better quality, and more quantity. As technology advances and more customers adapt to the knowledge that Lab Grown Diamonds are real diamonds, their true worth becomes clear. They are becoming part of every milestone moment today, while representing the sustainable choice for tomorrow.</p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion"
          }
        }
      },
